In this article, President Joseph R. Biden Jr. announces the termination of the national emergency declared at the southern border of the United States. He states that the declaration was unwarranted and declares that no more American taxpayer dollars will be used to construct a border wall. President Biden also mentions that a careful review of all resources appropriated or redirected to this purpose will be conducted. He concludes by informing Congress that the national emergency declared by Proclamation 9844 is terminated and the authorities invoked will no longer be used to construct a wall at the southern border.